<subSubSection id="1C8A6552A537891A8CE74C388926369A" pageId="41" pageNumber="314" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="542F36D9A537891A8CE74C38896237FA" blockId="41.[151,756,1289,1921]" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA537891A8CE74C38890E343A" bold="true" box="[151,258,1289,1313]" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">Remarks:</emphasis>
In the original description, 
<bibRefCitation id="30014B28A537891A8E4A4C3888CB345A" author="WARNCKE, K." pageId="41" pageNumber="314" pagination="747 - 801" refId="ref71068" refString="WARNCKE, K. 1992: 2. Beitrag zur Systematik und Verbreitung der Gattung Prosopis F. in der Westpalaarktis (Hym., Apidae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 24 (2): 747 - 801." type="journal article" year="1992">WARNCKE (1992: 769)</bibRefCitation>
classifies the species in the subgenus “ 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA537891A8EE04C1B8AE5345A" authorityName="FABRICIUS" authorityYear="1804" box="[656,745,1322,1345]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Prosopis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="41" pageNumber="314" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA537891A8EE04C1B8AE5345A" box="[656,745,1322,1345]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">Prosopis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (= 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA537891A8CC74C788901347A" authorityName="FABRICIUS" authorityYear="1793" box="[183,269,1353,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA537891A8CC74C788901347A" box="[183,269,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">Hylaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7DD757B0A537891A8D624C7B8947347A" box="[274,331,1353,1377]" pageId="41" pageNumber="314" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
) between 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA537891A8DC84C7B8A32347A" authorityName="FORSTER" authorityYear="1871" box="[440,574,1353,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tyrolensis">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA537891A8DC84C7B8A32347A" box="[440,574,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">H. tyrolensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA537891A8E014C7B8AE2347A" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[625,750,1353,1377]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funereus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA537891A8E014C7B8AE2347A" box="[625,750,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">H. funereus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to our understanding, these species belong to different subgenera. In fact, 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA537891A8D9E4CBB8A7A34BA" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[494,630,1418,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torquatus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA537891A8D9E4CBB8A7A34BA" box="[494,630,1418,1441]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">H. torquatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has special characteristics sui generis, which call both classifications into question. We recognize a closer comparability only with 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA537891A8D754CDB8974371A" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[261,376,1513,1537]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sidensis">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA537891A8D754CDB8974371A" box="[261,376,1513,1537]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">H. sidensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with which it shares the following characters: the short, apically broadened gonoforcipes of the males, in both sexes the dense strong punctation of the head and mesosoma, so that the sculpture appears matt; the lateral areae of the propodeum are arched without posterior ridge; the white mask is dorsally transversally truncated. The face of the female is completely black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="542F36D9A537891A8CE74FD88926369A" blockId="41.[151,756,1289,1921]" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">
<bibRefCitation id="30014B28A537891A8CE74FD88959361A" author="WARNCKE, K." box="[151,341,1769,1793]" pageId="41" pageNumber="314" pagination="747 - 801" refId="ref71068" refString="WARNCKE, K. 1992: 2. Beitrag zur Systematik und Verbreitung der Gattung Prosopis F. in der Westpalaarktis (Hym., Apidae). - Linzer biologische Beitrage 24 (2): 747 - 801." type="journal article" year="1992">WARNCKE (1992)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="93904D5AA537891A8DA34FDB8A54361A" baseAuthorityName="WARNCKE" baseAuthorityYear="1992" box="[467,600,1770,1793]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Hylaeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="314" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torquatus">
<emphasis id="66E4EACBA537891A8DA34FDB8A54361A" box="[467,600,1770,1793]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">H. torquatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Mardin and recorded it simultaneously from Hakkâri and Siirt as well as from 
<collectingCountry id="2C877649A537891A8D224E188987365A" box="[338,395,1833,1857]" name="Syria" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">Syria</collectingCountry>
. Since then the species has not been found again. It is only sparsely collected in 
<collectingCountry id="2C877649A537891A8ED94E788AF8367A" box="[681,756,1865,1889]" name="Turkey" pageId="41" pageNumber="314">Turkey</collectingCountry>
(3 provinces).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
